snippet.textDisplay: I am from India but I admit that Pakistan is a reservoir of musical and cultural talent. Being grounded and sticking to the very roots always unleashes the purity in compositions, something that more or less seems to have got diluted in the Indian subcontinent. Not that we don't have enough talent but they are not being channelised in the right direction. But Pakistani vocalists, lyricists and music arrangers are doing a great job by keeping themselves set on the right track. Beautiful composition portraying out of the world lyrics and a wonderful baritone by the singer.  Mesmerising to say the least. Truly, music knows no boundaries. In fact, it is capable of breaking all boundaries. Love from India.
